CMS Made Simple
http://cmsmadesimple.org

For information on installation, see INSTALL.

For information on upgrading your installion from a previous version, see 
UPGRADE.

CMS uses the smarty template engine in various places.  Their license and 
various documentation files are located in the smarty subdirectory of this 
distribution.

CMS uses GetText.php for internationalization.  GetText.php is released 
under the LGPL and is located here: 
http://phptal.sourceforge.net/bagpack/GetText/index.html

CMS uses HTMLArea 3.0 as it's content WYSIWYG.  HTMLArea is released under 
the htmlArea license (based on the BSD license) and is located at: 
http://www.interactivetools.com/products/htmlarea/
